1. Package Manager Installation:--
----------------------------------
1.1 first check the operation system of kernel -> cat /etc/os-release| cat /etc/redhat-release ->(to check the os version)
Reason:- Mongodb repository URL depends on the OS version.

1.2 create MongoDB repository file and add Official repo
vi /etc/yum.repo.d/mongodb-org-8.0 -> assume the file name 
[mongodb-org-8.0] ----> version of mongod.service(mongodb)| This is the repository ID (repo name).
name=MongoDB Repository  ---> This is the human readable of repository||Repository display name
baseurl=https://repo.mongodb.org/yum/redhat/9/mongodb-org/8.0/x86_64/  ---->Location of MongoDB packages 
gpgcheck=1  -----> Security verification
enabled=1  -------> Activate repo
gpgkey=https://pgp.mongodb.com/server-7.0.asc --------> Public key for package verification
explaintion of this url for our understand:- https://repo.mongodb.org/yum/redhat/9/mongodb-org/8.0/x86_64/
https:- secure protocol
repo.mongodb.org:- offical mongodb repository server
yum :- repository format of yum/dnf
redhat :- operating system type
9 :- version of rhel
mongodb-org :- mongodb community packages
8.0 :- mongodb version
x86_64 :- CPU architecture

gpgcheck=1 :-This enables GPG signature verification.(always admin prefere enable(1))
enable verification means 1 | disable verification means 2

gpgkey=https://pgp.mongodb.com/server-7.0.asc :- this means GPG public key location. |||| used to verify before installation.

MongoDB package
        ↓
Check GPG signature
        ↓
Verify using server-7.0.asc key
        ↓
If valid → install

1.3 dnf makecache ---> It creates or refreshes the local cache of repository data.||| this command first read the repo file and and connect to mongo server then download metadata and store it in cache(memory).

1.4 dnf install mongodb-org :- this command use to install the all mongodb-org packages
this will do first search repo file and download the RPM package then verify GPG key and install dependencies and install MongoDB.

1.5 systemctl start mongod.service :---> start the service

1.6 systemctl enable mongod.service :----> enable the service
